{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f43a5445-7664-4c4e-bc54-450facece8e5","content":"We have `dotnet` available but I need two things:\n\n1. **Where is your `.dmp` file?** Please provide the full path.\n2. I'll install `dotnet-dump` — the cross-platform tool for analyzing .NET crash dumps.\n\nOnce you share the path, I'll run commands like these to investigate:\n\n```\ndotnet-dump analyze <your.dmp>\n```\n\nKey commands inside the analyzer:\n- **`pe`** — print the last exception (often the crash cause)\n- **`clrstack`** — managed call stack of the crashing thread\n- **`threads`** — list all managed threads\n- **`dso`** — dump stack objects\n- **`eeheap`** — heap summary\n\nGo ahead and share the dump file path and I'll get started!","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ec7fbbfe-df33-44d2-a1a9-5a5a96b17ede","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"We have `dotnet` but not `dotnet-dump` installed yet. And there's no .dmp file in the current directory. Let me ask the user for the path to their dump file and install dotnet-dump.","outputTokens":252,"requestId":"6080:C5472:2F76FE:3E0902:69FFE57F"},"id":"cef9d5ef-158f-47c3-8d6d-ef554013c44b","timestamp":"2026-05-10T01:55:20.348Z","parentId":"aa9cb7d0-835f-4219-96d9-a5fe78072c7b"}
